了绝望的色彩。面对普遍不受欢迎的情况，努力保持权力。 His far-right coalition partners have pushed for a prolonged war to destroy Hamas in Gaza, and are now demanding that he take action against Iran. In Lebanon and elsewhere, Israel has often hit back against sources of fire and against senior commanders.在伊朗，潜在的目标可能会有所不同：伊朗的铀浓缩和其他核设施长期以来一直在他们的视线范围内；伊斯兰革命卫队基地；或者可能是制造无人机和导弹的设施。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;然而，由于以色列在加沙上孤立自己，这些袭击表明以色列的广泛安全如何依赖于其他国家他们不太热衷于升级。 Many missiles and drones were shot down by American, British and French forces before they reached Israel. Jordan helped too, destroying Iranian weapons in their own air space, and other Arab states may have been involved indirectly.以色列在美国的广泛帮助下开发了自己的分层防空系统，完成了剩下的工作。 They include the Arrow missile that intercepts ballistic missiles in space;大卫弹弓和爱国者试图在重返大气层时攻击他们； and Iron Dome designed for smaller artillery, rockets and drones. When it comes to attacking Iran, Israel has the required jets and refuelling tankers—not to mention drones, missiles and submarines. But the more help it gets from the United States, the more powerful a blow it can deliver.例如，以色列飞机最好得到美国搜救能力的支持，以帮助任何被击落的飞行员。</p>;<div class="adComponent_advert__kPVUI adComponent_incontent__boSCu adComponent_hidden_​​_Dp0GM css-0 e1cbnkh80">;<div>;<div id= "econ-2" class="adComponent_adcontainer__eooQr">;</div>;</div>;</div>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;内塔尼亚胡先生必须衡量他还承受了多少压力可以重视与以色列重要保护者美国的关系。 He knows that Mr Shamir lost the election in 1992 in part because ties with America soured over settlement building.伊朗的袭击暂时弥合了拜登和内塔尼亚胡之间的裂痕，他们一直因以色列在加沙发动战争而存在分歧。但重大报复将危及这一点。通过将以色列纳入中央司令部的责任区，美国一直致力于整合该地区的防空系统。 Still, Arab states have no desire to be caught in a war between Iran, which they fear, and Israel, which they cannot openly support.英国首相里希·苏纳克 (Rishi Sunak) 也劝阻报复：“没有人希望看到更多流血事件，”他说。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;所有这一切表明以色列面临拜登等人的巨大压力，要求其表现出克制。在该国战时内阁与内塔尼亚胡的竞争对手本尼·甘茨会面之前，他建议以色列可以等待时机。 “We will build a regional coalition and exact the price from Iran in the fashion and timing that is right for us.”然而，即使以色列不反击，美国长期存在的伊朗问题也会卷土重来。 Ahead of the presidential election in November.共和党候选人唐纳德·特朗普将此次袭击归咎于拜登在海外的“软弱”。 Despite their demands for tough action, few Republicans relish the prospect of being sucked into war against Iran.尽管如此，拜登可能会被迫恢复类似于特朗普对伊朗“最大压力”的政策，包括对伊朗实施更严厉的禁运。由于中国和俄罗斯不愿意实施制裁，这可能比过去更加困难。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;拜登先生也不想破坏已经存在的制裁试图确保安全的前景令人畏惧加沙的短期停火、交换人质和囚犯，以及在理想的情况下启动政治进程，将沙特与以色列的正常化协议与巴勒斯坦建国进程结合起来。 In 1991 America was at the zenith of its power after the end of the cold war. By contrast Mr Biden has attempted to extricate America from the troubles of the Middle East, and found it impossible. 1991 年明显的旧模式正在重新出现：当以色列与无国籍的巴勒斯坦人交战时，以色列的朋友就会分裂；当以色列与无国籍的巴勒斯坦人交战时，以色列的朋友就会分裂； when it is attacked by radical states such as Iraq and Iran, they rally behind it. Mr Biden has mustered an undeclared international coalition to defend Israeli skies.他已致电<small>;G</small>;领导人讨论对伊朗的回应。 <small>;联合国</small>;安理会也将处理此事。拜登先生从 1991 年汲取了另一个教训：越多外部势力对抗以色列的敌人，以色列本身就越有可能采取克制行动。<span class="ufinish">;■</span>;</p>;</div >; https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2024/04/14/will-israel-retaliate-against-iran-or-hold-back /内容/tua2i3fununsms89n1h60htcd31m8gv8 Sun, 14 Apr 2024 18:33:11 GMT伊朗以色列
